OL,6,FProsecutor Hannah Baddeley said: "The
OL,7,Fdefendant failed to disclose to the
OL,8,FDepartment for Works and Pensions
OL,9,F(DWP) that his wife was in employment
OL,10,Fwhile claiming jobseekers' allowance,
OL,11,Fhousing benefit and income support. In
OL,12,Ftotal he claimed #57,774.46 between
OL,13,FMarch 31, 2009 and January 14, 2019."
OL,15,FMiss Baddeley said the initial claim
OL,16,Fwas legitimate.
